Folio Communications Limited, publishers of Daily Times, has appointed Mr Omokioja Julius Eto as Editor. Also appointed are: Dr. Ise-Oluwa Ige as Chairman, Editorial Board/Group Managing Editor and Mr Samuel Nzeh as Standards/Special Publications Editor. A statement by Managing Director, Mr Aliu Akoshile, said the appointments, which took effect from on Wednesday, would herald the beginning of the next phase of the revival and repositioning of Daily Times. Eto holds a Masterâ€™s degree in Political Science from the University of Lagos (1995) and a Post-Graduate Diploma from the Nigeria Institute of Journalism (NIJ), among other certifications. He was, until recently the News Editor, Deputy/Associate Editor of The Guardian.